---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LegalHeader from "../../components/LegalHeader.astro";
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from "../../i18n/ui";

const lastUpdated = "Last updated: 13 May 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Retro Pal's privacy policy. No data collected, transmitted, or stored outside your device."
>
  <div class="page-shell legal-page">
    <LegalHeader
      kicker="Privacy Policy"
      title="Privacy"
      updated={lastUpdated}
      intro="Retro Pal collects no personal data. No usage statistics, no unique identifiers, no cookies, no analytics. This page explains in detail how the app handles your data — which is to say, almost not at all."
    />

    <article class="prose">
      <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        The publisher of Retro Pal and this site is a French micro-enterprise (auto-entrepreneur),
        based in Paris. Full contact details (legal name, SIRET, address, publication director)
        are available on the <a href="/en/legal">Legal notice</a> page.
      </p>
      <p>
        For any question about your personal data, write to
        <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Data collected by the app</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>None.</strong> Retro Pal collects no personal data, no device identifier, no usage
        statistics, and sends no telemetry. The app is designed to run entirely offline and contains
        no third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDK.
      </p>
      <p>Concretely, this means:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>No internet connection is required for the app to work.</li>
        <li>No IP address, no advertising identifier (IDFA), no device identifier (IDFV) is read, retained or transmitted.</li>
        <li>No event is logged (no "user opened the app", "user launched a game", etc.).</li>
        <li>No cookies, web beacons, or tracking pixels are used, neither in the app nor on this site (the site is fully static, with no third-party scripts).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Data stored locally on your device</h2>
      <p>
        To work, Retro Pal stores certain data <strong>only on your iPhone</strong>, in the app's
        sandbox:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The ROM files you import (which you must own legally).</li>
        <li>Game saves (battery saves and save states).</li>
        <li>Your preferences (language, controls, default speed, etc.).</li>
        <li>Cumulative playtime per game, used purely for cosmetic display on share cards.</li>
        <li>The cheat codes you enter (Pro).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        This data never leaves your device. It is included in the iOS iCloud Backup if you have it
        enabled at the system level, but that backup is managed by Apple, not by Retro Pal, and is
        itself encrypted by Apple.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies and similar technologies on this site</h2>
      <p>
        This site (retropal.fr) is fully static. It sets no cookies, uses no local storage, and
        loads no third-party scripts (no Google Analytics, no Meta Pixel, no Hotjar, nothing).
        No consent banner is required because no consent is required.
      </p>
      <p>
        The fonts used (VT323, Newsreader, JetBrains Mono) are self-hosted on our own servers,
        not loaded from Google Fonts or a third-party CDN. No information about your visit is
        transmitted to a third party.
      </p>

      <h2>5. In-app purchases via the App Store</h2>
      <p>
        Retro Pal Pro purchases ($4.99 lifetime or $0.99 per month) are processed
        <strong>exclusively by Apple via StoreKit</strong>. No payment information passes through
        Retro Pal. Apple acts as the direct seller and remits a share to us per the Apple Developer
        Program terms.
      </p>
      <p>
        For billing, refund, or subscription management questions, consult Apple's privacy policy
        and App Store help:
        <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" rel="noopener">apple.com/legal/privacy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Sharing screenshots</h2>
      <p>
        When you use the "Share screenshot" function from the pause menu or via a system screenshot,
        Retro Pal generates an image locally on your device. This image is shared only at the moment
        <em>you</em> choose to share it, via the standard iOS share sheet. Sharing is then handled
        by the app you pick (Messages, Photos, Mail, etc.), and Retro Pal has no visibility into
        the destination or content of the share.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and applicable French data protection
        law, you have rights of access, rectification, erasure, objection, restriction, and
        portability concerning your personal data.
      </p>
      <p>
        Since no personal data is collected or retained by Retro Pal, these rights are de facto
        automatically respected. If you uninstall the app, all your local data is removed from
        your device.
      </p>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with France's data protection authority,
        the CNIL: <a href="https://www.cnil.fr" rel="noopener">cnil.fr</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        This policy may be updated if the app's functionality evolves (for example, if an opt-in
        iCloud sync feature is added later). Any substantive change will be flagged by updating
        the "Last updated" date at the top of this page, and via an in-app notice if the change
        implies new data processing.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For any question, comment, or complaint regarding this privacy policy, contact
        <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page { padding-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem); }
  .legal-page .prose { max-width: 68ch; margin-inline: 0; }
</style>
